                <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                      <locus from = "#iiv(erso)" to = "#iiir(ecto)"/>
                        The Gə‘əz alphabet, with each letter’s numerical value.‎
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                      <locus target = "#iiir(ecto)"/>
                      Asmāt prayer to protect domestic animals from wild animals. ‎
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                      ‎Prayer for <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል:</foreign>, in a crude hand,
                      <locus target ="#25r #44v #128r"/>, and ‎passim;
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ ስላሴ፡</foreign>, <locus target = "#16v #36r #118r"/> and passim. ‎
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id = "e4">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">‎Note of ownership by the monastery of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ደብረ፡ ገነት፡</foreign>,
                      in a crude ‎hand, <locus target = "#iv #175v"/>; <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ጋብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>, <locus target = "#135v"/>
                      (the name of his wife ‎and children insufficiently legible), and <locus target ="#175v"/>;
                      and <foreign xml:lang ="gez">ዘወልደ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign>, <locus target ="#176v #177r"/>. ‎</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e5">
                        ‎Columetric layout of text <locus target = "#146r #146v"/> (tenth biblical canticle> <locus target = "ms_i1.2.10"/>). ‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e6">
                        ‎The scribe has addressed the problem of lines of text that are too ‎long for the folio mainly in the selection of an
                        aspect ratio that ‎leaves ample room for the lines of text.  Occasionally, a line of text ‎is still too long to fit on
                        the folio; in such cases the scribe ‎completes the text above the end of the line (e.g., <locus target = "#7r #10v #22r"/>, ‎etc.)
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e7">
                        ‎Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#7r #19r #49v #‎‎59r #71r #87r"/>, etc.)
                        and overlooked lines of text are written ‎interlinearly (<locus target = "#47v #77v #91v #95r #121r #146r"/>)‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e8">
                        ‎<locus target = "#iv"/> pen trial, <date calendar = "ethiopian" when = "1943"><foreign xml:lang="gez">መጋቢት፡</foreign> 12, [19]43 EC (March 21, 1951 CE)</date>.‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e9">
                        <locus target ="#ir #iir #iiiv"/> and <locus from ="176v" to = "177v"/> are blank, save for some scrawls.‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e10">
                        Copied by <foreign xml:lang = "gez">በርተሎሜዎስ፡</foreign>

                      </item>

                  </list>
